fields.description:
When I use DNS to address a service I normally expect the service's URL to have the following format:

{noformat}http://compute.mycloud.example.com:8773/{noformat}

This works fine for most of the user-facing services, but at least two services require service paths regardless of whether they were addressed with their DNS names or not:

{noformat}http://bootstrap.mycloud.example.com:8773/services/Empyrean/
http://properties.mycloud.example.com:8773/services/Properties/{noformat}

This inconsistency doesn't make much sense from a user's standpoint, doubly so for the bootstrap/empyrean service, which requires two _different_ names in the same URL.  To make eucalyptus 4.2 shippable I could make euare-useraddkey add paths to those specific services when it writes config files, but that would just paper over the inconsistency without actually fixing it.
